Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Line a #baking sheet{} with #foil{}. Wash and dry produce.

Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Pick and roughly chop fronds from @dill{1/4%ounce}.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken and sear, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{4-8%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in the next step).

Turn off heat; transfer chicken to one side of prepared baking sheet.

> Swap in chicken for pork. Cook until browned and cooked through, 3-5 minutes per side. Transfer to a cutting board to rest (skip the baking sheet—no need to roast!).

Add green beans to empty side of baking sheet with chicken; toss with a drizzle of olive oil, salt, pepper, and @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} to taste.

Roast on top rack until green beans are tender and chicken is cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Remove from oven; transfer chicken to a #cutting board{} to rest for ~{5%minutes}.

> Roast green beans without chicken.

Meanwhile, add @Israeli couscous{2.5%ounce} and @butter{1%tablespoon} to a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Cook, stirring, until butter has melted and couscous is lightly toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @water{3/4%cup}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, and a big pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until couscous is tender, ~{6-8%minutes}.

> Drain excess water if necessary.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While couscous cooks, heat pan used for chicken over medium-high heat. Add @chicken stock concentrate{1} and @water{1/4%cup}; bring to a simmer and cook ~{1-2%minutes}.

Reduce heat to low and whisk in @sour cream{3%tablespoon}, half the chopped dill, and @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon} to taste. Turn off heat. Stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} and any resting juices from chicken. Season with salt and pepper.

Fluff couscous with a #fork{} and season with salt and pepper.

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide couscous, chicken, and green beans between plates. Spoon sauce over chicken and sprinkle with remaining chopped dill and any remaining chili flakes to taste. Serve.

> Slice chicken crosswise.
> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.